-- Willis to Buy Avalon to Expand Broker’s Business in Canada
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-11-29T18:12:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-29/willis-to-buy-avalon-to-expand-broker-s-business-in-canada.html
Willis Group Holdings Plc (WSH) , the
third-largest insurance broker, agreed to buy Avalon Actuarial
Inc. to expand in Canada.  Avalon’s Jean-Robert Elie will serve as the buyer’s
executive vice president and Canadian human capital practice
leader after the deal is completed, London-based Willis said
today in a Globe Newswire statement that didn’t disclose terms.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary Tracer in New York at 
 ztracer1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
